The paper discusses the security of networks and the design of defense mechanisms against malicious attacks, which falls under the category of computer security (cs.CR). The paper also discusses the role of network design in mitigating the inefficiencies of decentralized defense, which falls under the category of computer networks (cs.NI). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of byzantine nodes in the model, which falls under the category of distributed computing (cs.DC). The paper also discusses the use of defense mechanisms that rely on individual behavior, which falls under the category of social and information networks (cs.SI). Finally, the paper proposes a model that uses artificial intelligence to optimize network design, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
